## Key Rules:
1. Use string.Template syntax ($var/${var}) in .template files — NOT jinja2
2. Conditional logic (if/else) goes in run.sh Python blocks, NOT in templates
3. All /mf/input/ and /mf/output/ paths follow MiQroForge conventions
4. MPI nodes MUST declare OMPI_ALLOW_RUN_AS_ROOT environment vars
5. Always include `# MF2 init` at the top of run.sh
6. Output the nodespec.yaml content first, then run.sh, separated by markers
7. Be concise — minimal necessary ports and parameters
